			<node ID="ID_147181514" TEXT="A system on chip (SoC / &#716; &#603; s &#716; o&#650; &#712; s i&#720; / es-oh-SEE or / s &#594; k / sock) is an integrated circuit (also known as a chip) that integrates all components of a computer or other electronic system.These components always include a central processing unit (CPU) memory input/output ports and secondary storage &#8211; all on a single substrate or microchip the size of a coin." />
			</node>
